qas.question: Historians estimate how much of magnates make up szlachta?
Out of one million szlachtas how many were magnates?
Out of one million how many people could be viewed with significant impact politically?

context: Some historians estimate the number of magnates as <a0_0>1%<a0_0/> of the number of szlachta. Out of approx. one million szlachta, tens of thousands of families, only <a1_0>200–300<a1_0/> persons could be classed as great magnates with country-wide possessions and influence, and <a2_0>30–40<a2_0/> of them could be viewed as those with significant impact on Poland's politics.
